      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2021-08-24</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2021-11-20T19:51:29Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Lowering Medicare Premiums and Prescription Drug Costs Act</b></p> <p>This bill transfers certain programs that provide Medicare premium and cost-sharing assistance for low-income individuals from Medicaid to Medicare.</p> <p>Specifically, the bill establishes a program under Medicare to assist low-income Medicare beneficiaries with premiums, coinsurance, deductibles, and other costs. Currently, such assistance is provided through Medicare Savings Programs, which are administered by state Medicaid programs.</p> <p> The bill also establishes a related special enrollment period under Medicare, expands eligibility for assistance to beneficiaries with income up to 200% of the federal poverty line, and provides for joint eligibility determinations with respect to the bill's program and the low-income subsidy program under the Medicare prescription drug benefit.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
